Rating: 4
I use fingerling potatoes (red, white, yellow, purple) from Costco and use roasted garlic olive oil. I do them on convection roast at 375 degrees for 35 minutes, add the rosemary and roast 10 to 15 minutes longer, until nicely browned. I serve them with various things, including a fantastic pot roast recipe I have and they always get rave reviews.

Rating: 2
It was OK. I thought the cooking time of an hour was too much. Next time I'd add the rosemary in at the beginning

Rating: 4
Simple and tasty. I always mess around with roasting potatoes, with inconsistant success. This recipe turns out great. I cooked it in my convection oven at 400 for about 30 min, stirring twice. Added the rosemary and it really only needed about 4 more minutes. I should have lowered the temp in general, but it worked out fine. The veggies were browned and delicious. Definately make sure your shallot and carrot are bigger than the potatoes, since they seemed to cook and brown faster. Also, I found that it all kind of shrank down, so keep that in mind when preparing for a crowd.

Rating: 4
Quick and easy. Will make again.

