Rating: 3
We paired this with our Easter ham and had good results. I roasted the potatoes through the first baking and then cooled and refrigerated them overnight. Shortly before serving I sprinkled with the rosemary and completed the roasting. It took longer than 15 minutes since they were cold.

Rating: 3
This was a great change from the ordinary roasted potatoes and carrots which accompany roast beef. The rosemary and roasted shallots provided a delicious variation and "dressed up" this traditional Sunday evening dinner!